29/07/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR searched three private firms providing security services in BiH on Thursday (28 July) morning, to determine whether they are operating in line with the Dayton Peace Agreement. 
In addition to searching the firms' headquarters in Sarajevo, Banja Luka and Mostar, raids were conducted on their other offices. 
The action was announced to local authorities and was completed without incident. 
Afterwards, weapons and ammunition were removed, including more than 20kg of TNT, according to EUFOR spokesperson Bruno Compagnone. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 29/07/05; OHR, FENA, PBS BiH - 28/07/05)
